equilibrium vapor pressure [24]. From
Eq. 5, it can be deduced that the rate of
sublimation accelerates with increase in temperature because the term Peq increased exponentially with temperature. Furthermore, the
surface morphology of the Ag NPs also affects the sublimation process as expressed
by the relationship with the radius of curvature (r) of Ag NPs6Pr=P∞exp2γMAg/rTρR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
